er all Unicode escape cases. Do we really need to retest existing logic flows, or can we just add a focused test for Unicode escape sequences?\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Evaluating nested literal documents**\\n\\nI'm looking at the existing method `createsNestedLiteralDocumentsWithoutRuntimeParsing`, which includes an escape sequence in its value for line breaks and a snowman character, but it doesn't seem to test for Unicode escapes. The key escape is currently handled through an interpolated key as the KeyEncoder, rather than the literal parser. So, exploring a new testing path for literal keys with escape sequences might be beneficial. I can also confirm that the value path is already set.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Exploring Unicode translation**\\n\\nI'm considering how Unicode translations work, particularly with `\\\"\\\\u005cu0020\\\"`. It seems it might become `\\\\u0020` after the first phase, but I wonder if there's a second phase involved. Does the translation process in Java handle this without recursion? I think it’s interesting that in a normal string, `\\\\u` isn’t valid. My mind is toying with all these aspects of escape sequences and their interpretations. It's a bit puzzling!\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_IYv0kTwRI5h2CFHP5dmOcxSA|fc_0f9d415ec00b6de3016a2a39b997788195ae04006a6074925f", "name": "edit", "arguments": {"path": "tests/src/io.circe/circe-literal_3/0.14.15/src/test/scala/io_circe/circe_literal_3/Circe_literal_3Test.scala", "edits": [{"oldText": "  @Test\n  def reportsCompileTimeErrorsForInvalidJsonAndMissingEncoders(): Unit = {", "newText": "  @Test\n  def decodesEscapedLiteralFieldNamesAndStringValues(): Unit = {\n    val document: Json = json\"\"\"\n      {\n        \"line\\nkey\": \"tab\\tcarriage\\rbackspace\\bformfeed\\fslash\\/quote\\\"backslash\\\\\",\n        \"quote\\\"key\": \"plain\"\n      }\n    \"\"\"\n\n    assertThat(document.hcursor.get[String](\"line\\nkey\"))\n      .isEqualTo(Right(\"tab\\tcarriage\\rbackspace\\bformfeed\\fslash/quote\\\"backslash\\\\\"))\n    assertThat(document.hcursor.get[String](\"quote\\\"key\")).isEqualTo(Right(\"plain\"))\n  }\n\n  @Test\n  def reportsCompileTimeErrorsForInvalidJsonAndMissingEncoders(): Unit = {"}]}, "partialJson": "{\"path\":\"tests/src/io.circe/circe-literal_3/0.14.15/src/test/scala/io_circe/circe_literal_3/Circe_literal_3Test.scala\",\"edits\":[{\"oldText\":\"  @Test\\n  def reportsCompileTimeErrorsForInvalidJsonAndMissingEncoders(): Unit = {\",\"newText\":\"  @Test\\n  def decodesEscapedLiteralFieldNamesAndStringValues(): Unit = {\\n    val document: Json = json\\\"\\\"\\\"\\n      {\\n        \\\"line\\\\nkey\\\": \\\"tab\\\\tcarriage\\\\rbackspace\\\\bformfeed\\\\fslash\\\\/quote\\\\\\\"backslash\\\\\\\\\\\",\\n        \\\"quote\\\\\\\"key\\\": \\\"plain\\\"\\n      }\\n    \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n\\n    assertThat(document.hcursor.get[String](\\\"line\\\\nkey\\\"))\\n      .isEqualTo(Right(\\\"tab\\\\tcarriage\\\\rbackspace\\\\bformfeed\\\\fslash/quote\\\\\\\"backslash\\\\\\\\\\\"))\\n    assertThat(document.hcursor.get[String](\\\"quote\\\\\\\"key\\\")).isEqualTo(Right(\\\"plain\\\"))\\n  }\\n\\n  @Test\\n  def reportsCompileTimeErrorsForInvalidJsonAndMissingEncoders(): Unit = {\"}]}"}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 793, "output": 1574, "cacheRead": 39424, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 41791, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1781152151548, "responseId": "resp_0f9d415ec00b6de3016a2a399826748195a7e71a91068f7369"}}
